        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "\r",
                  "// Guardar token en una variable de colección\r",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('api_slack_auth_token', response.data.access_token);\r",
                  "\r",
                  "// Opcional: mostrar en consola\r",
                  "console.log('Token guardado:', response.data.access_token);\r",
                  "console.log(pm.collectionVariables.get('api_slack_auth_token'))"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "",
                "value": "",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"email\": \"mati.dev.gimenez@gmail.com\",\r\n    \"password\": \"Mati_123\" \r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{API_SLACK_URL}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{API_SLACK_URL}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Authenticates a user with their email and password credentials.\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST {{API_SLACK_URL}}/api/auth/login`\n\n## Request Body\n\n| Field      | Type   | Description              |\n|------------|--------|--------------------------|\n| `email`    | string | The user's email address |\n| `password` | string | The user's password      |\n\n**Example:**\n```json\n{\n    \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"yourPassword\"\n}\n```\n\n## Response\n\nOn success, returns a `200 OK` with a JSON body containing:\n\n- `ok` (boolean): `true` if authentication was successful.\n- `status` (number): HTTP status code.\n- `message` (string): Confirmation message.\n- `data.access_token` (string): JWT token to be used for authenticated requests.\n\n**Example response:**\n```json\n{\n    \"ok\": true,\n    \"status\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Usuario autentificado exitosamente\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"access_token\": \"<JWT_TOKEN>\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Upon a successful login, the `access_token` is automatically saved to the collection variable `api_slack_auth_token` via the test script, making it available for subsequent authenticated requests."
          },
          "response": []
        }
